FBIS4-26524 "drchi121_o_94010" FBIS-CHI-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Shanghai's Outskirts Attract Foreign Investment Shanghai's Outskirts Attract Foreign Investment OW2206075594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0725 GMT 22 Jun 94 OW2206075594 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Shanghai, June 22 (XINHUA) -- The outskirts of Shanghai have become a favorable place for overseas investment. Altogether 3,204 enterprises with overseas investment, accounting for 46 percent of the city's total, have been set up on the outskirts. They involve a sum of 3.04 billion U.S. dollars. According to Lu Nanxing, an official of the municipal commission of agriculture, 52 percent of these enterprises have ties with Hong Kong, 16.2 percent with Taiwan, 11.6 percent with the United States and 8.8 percent with Japan. Lu noted that a number of these enterprises have formed enterprise groups so as to better compete on the market.
